      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-01-06T21:10:35Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yeah, that\u0027s right.  This snippet of code will prevent us from JITing,\n\n        if (SK_ARRAY_COUNT(arg) \u003c fImpl-\u003estrides.size()) {\n            return false;                                                  \n        }                                        \n\nand Program::eval() will then find jit_entry \u003d\u003d nullptr, then fall through to the interpreter.  It\u0027ll work no matter what, but you won\u0027t necessarily be able to say, assert(program.hasJIT()).\n\n(fImpl-\u003estrides[i] is the number of bytes to increment each pointer by as we loop, generally 0 for uniform pointers and sizeof(T) for varying pointers.  But you could do neat things with negative strides or \u003esizeof(T) or \u003csizeof(T) potentially.)",
      "parentUuid": "5edbdbb0_0c1f3dd8",
